    "In addition, different particles can be produced at different times or regions as the system freezes out, or through meson-baryon interactions.",
    "The measurements of Λ and Λ polarization in √ s NN = 7.7 -39 GeV show no dif- ference within current uncertainties.",
    "Therefore, to establish the global nature of the polarization, it is very important to measure the polarization of different particles, and if possible, particles of different spins.Global polarization leaves its imprint on vector mesons such as (1020) and K * 0 (892).",
